SALMONELLOSIS, SESAME SEED PRODUCT - AUSTRALIA (NEW SOUTH WALES)
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon, 7 Apr 2003
From: Martyn Kirk <Martyn.Kirk@dhs.vic.gov.au>
Source: OzFoodNet, Australia [edited]

Australian _Salmonella Montevideo_ outbreak linked to imported tahini.
--------------------------------------------------
Cases of _S. Montevideo_ are being notified in Australia, principally in
New South Wales, with 54 Australian cases detected since 1 Nov 2002.
The implicated imported tahini has been recalled. Information from
interviews with new cases in conjunction with food sample testing are
suggesting possible links with other sources of tahini.
Countries detecting an increase of _S. Montevideo_ cases could ask about
history of travel to Australia and consumption of sesame seed-based foods.
A PFGE pattern of outbreak isolates is available.
For further inquires:
Leanne Unicomb <lunic@doh.health.nsw.gov.au>
