[Tahini is a paste made from raw sesame seeds. Other products made from
sesame seeds include hummus and halvah.
Previous outbreaks of salmonellosis have been associated with food products
produced from sesame seeds. As reported in a previous ProMED posting
(Salmonella typhimurium DT104 - Australia, Europe 20010822.1980), between
1985 and 2001 the National Enteric Pathogen Surveillance Scheme (NEPSS) in
Australia has recorded the isolation of 17 different _Salmonella_ spp. from
sesame seeds and sesame seed products, including hummus, tahini, and
halvah, on 30 occasions. Sesame seed products should be always be
considered when attempting to identify a source of salmonellosis. - Mod.LL]
